SEMDL Help Topic: reference add

Usage:
- `ssd add <kind> <file> [field=value ...]`
- `ssd add <kind> <file> [field=value ...] --dry-run`

Status:
- The current slice supports inline structural kinds: `resource`, `segment`, `assertion`, `hypothesis`, `alternative`.
- `provenance`, `annotation`, and sidecar-targeted add remain deferred.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help troubleshooting`

Sample:
- `ssd add resource docs/examples/minimal.ssd id=R2 type=appendix label=月次売上補足 --dry-run`
